A lot of folks may not know this, but my mama is a gigantic, crazed, and loyal fan of Elvis Presley @elvis. So much that I was this close 🤏 to being named Elvis Tidwell. Thankfully my dad stepped in and offered up Travis as a compromise. So they met in the middle and nicknamed me Trelvis my whole life!! So it’s only right I put my name up in lights like the King had but with my own title😎. Screaming “CONGRATULATIONS” to my longtime buddy @jellyroll615 for these WINS! If you would have told me when we were making the ‘Goodnight Nashville’ album that he was gonna be here, I would have told you I KNOW!!! Just a matter of time. Seriously so happy for you brother and the hard work is clearly evident!!! 
•

•

•

When I played with @therealbigsmo, Jelly would come out on tour runs with us, not even to perform always but just to kick it on the road with us when he had down time. What times we had!! Then of course I finally got to work with him when I really really needed work at one time and he gave it to me. The result was Goodnight Nashville. I will never forget when we come up with Echoes. We knew. Working with Jelly got me the gig with Upchurch and that’s how they collaborated on Ryan’s King Of Dixie album with “Runnin On Fumes”. Fun song too! There’s your info today for Tidwell’s Tidbits. #blessed #love #life #fun #music #jellyroll #cmtawards #winning #winner #davidray #godisgood #nashville #goodnightnashville #session #musiccity #songwriter #talent #country #rock #rap
